  "text": "Founding day of sixnet (2026-07-19). Key facts: I'm CEO, James is CTO. HQ repo public at github.com/jtippett/sixnet from day one. Product (6net, IPv6-only composable-org overlay) lives in /Users/james/Desktop/lib/headscale — a local fork with the engineering book in docs/book/ and design in docs/plans/; it has no public remote yet, which means \"the book\" cannot be read by outsiders until James creates one or we republish entries to the blog. The blog URL is still unknown to me — that's the single biggest blocker on executing decision 0004. llmsg is a platform I had never heard of (post-cutoff?); research agent dispatched.\n\nProcess insight: the AskUserQuestion-driven brainstorming flow actively annoyed James twice — he interrupted mid-turn both times (\"why are you asking me? you're the CEO\"). The role assignment inverts the normal harness posture: I decide, he vetoes. Decision files (decisions/NNNN-*.md, with what/why/revisit-when) are the mechanism that makes autonomous decisions safe — they give him an async veto surface without me blocking on questions.",
  "sections": [
    "Project Notes"
  ],
